From: Zijun Hu <zijun.hu@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Jun 2025 20:31:17 +0800
Subject: Bluetooth: hci_sync: Use bt_dev_err() to log error message in
 hci_update_event_filter_sync()
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc1
Git-commit: da0186f19a7433d3d5607b0f61e9a3de17d1f721
References: jsc#PED-14261

Use bt_dev_err() instead of bt_dev_dbg() to log error message in
hci_update_event_filter_sync().

Signed-off-by: Zijun Hu <zijun.hu@oss.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Luiz Augusto von Dentz <luiz.von.dentz@intel.com>
Acked-by: Chun-Yi Lee <jlee@suse.com>
---
 net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c
+++ b/net/bluetooth/hci_sync.c
@@ -6117,7 +6117,7 @@ static int hci_update_event_filter_sync(
 						 &b->bdaddr,
 						 HCI_CONN_SETUP_AUTO_ON);
 		if (err)
-			bt_dev_dbg(hdev, "Failed to set event filter for %pMR",
+			bt_dev_err(hdev, "Failed to set event filter for %pMR",
 				   &b->bdaddr);
 		else
 			scan = SCAN_PAGE;
